  "body_html": "<!DOCTYPE html\n  SYSTEM \"about:legacy-compat\">\n<html lang=\"en-us\" dir=\"ltr\"><head><title>SAP Query</title><meta charset=\"utf-8\"><link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"screen,projection\" href=\"/resource/css/style-v2.css\"><script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"js/sap-strings.js\"></script></head><body class=\"en-us sap-light centered navigation-default enumeration-disabled\"><div id=\"d4h5-main-container\" class=\"container_12\" role=\"application\"><div id=\"d4h5-section-container\" class=\"grid_12\"><div id=\"d4h5-main-content\" class=\"grid_8 alpha omega\"><section><div class=\"page topic  - topic-topic \" id=\"loio2d09da531198434de10000000a174cb4\"><h1 class=\"title topictitle1\">SAP Query </h1><div class=\"body\">\n<div class=\"section\"><section class=\"section\" type=\"Definition\"><h2 class=\"section_title\">Definition</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">You can use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">SAP Query</span> tool to define reports without having to carry out any programming. You can also include your\nown data. </p>\n</section></div>\n<div class=\"section\"><section class=\"section\" type=\"Use\"><h2 class=\"section_title\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">In this component, you can use the following queries: </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\"><li class=\"li\"><p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Overview of Limits</span>\n</p></li><li class=\"li\"><p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Overview of Limit Utilizations</span>\n</p></li></ul>\n<p class=\"p\">You can use the queries offered here as examples. Alternatively, you can use these reports: <a class=\"xref\" href=\"c609da531198434de10000000a174cb4.html\">Displaying an Overview of Limits</a> and <a class=\"xref\" href=\"c909da531198434de10000000a174cb4.html\">Displaying\nUtilizations</a>. You can copy these using the standard<span class=\"ph uicontrol\"> SAP Query</span> tool by choosing <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><img src=\"themes/sap-light/img/navstart.gif\" alt=\"Start of the navigation path\" title=\"Start of the navigation path\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Tools</span>&nbsp;<img src=\"themes/sap-light/img/navstep.gif\" alt=\"Next navigation step\" title=\"Next navigation step\">&nbsp;<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">SAP Query</span><img src=\"themes/sap-light/img/navend.gif\" alt=\"End of the navigation path\" title=\"End of the navigation path\"></span> and then use them as a template for the queries and infosets you define yourself. </p>\n</section></div>\n<div class=\"section\"><section class=\"section\" type=\"Integration\"><h2 class=\"section_title\">Integration</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">SAP Query</span> tool is a standard tool. You can view the documentation about the general usage of SAP queries in <a class=\"xref\" href=\"4e5615eb43184f47e10000000a42189e.html\" title=\"\">Query</a>. </p>\n</section></div>\n</div></div></section><div class=\"clear\"></div>\n</div></div></div></body></html>"
